# Copy to `.env.local` for local development. Never commit real secrets.
#
# Environments:
# - Local: `.env.local` (loaded by Next.js automatically).
# - Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables — scope each name to:
#     Production  → deploys from `main`
#     Preview     → PRs + branches (incl. `staging` preview); use staging/sandbox values
#     Development → optional, for `vercel dev`
# See docs/deployment-vercel.md for the full matrix and staging-branch workflow.

# --- Public (exposed to the browser; must use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix) ---

# Canonical site URL for metadata, redirects, or absolute links when needed.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# --- Server-only (never NEXT_PUBLIC_) ---

# Transactional email (e.g. Resend) when contact or notifications are implemented.
# RESEND_API_KEY=

# --- Sanity CMS (when the app reads/writes Sanity content) ---

# NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_DATASET=production
# SANITY_API_READ_TOKEN=
# SANITY_API_WRITE_TOKEN=

# NODE_ENV is set by Node / your host; do not set it in committed env files.
